## Branch naming (required)

- `fix/<what>-<YYYYMMDD>`, `feat/<what>-<YYYYMMDD>`, `perf/<what>-<YYYYMMDD>`, `refactor/<what>-<YYYYMMDD>`
- No random animal names. `git branch` output should be self-explanatory.
- One branch per task. Merge to main when verified, not when compiled.

---

## Before calling something done

- [ ] Did I actually build what I claim? (`git diff` / file read)
- [ ] Re-ran tests relevant to the change?
- [ ] Clean rebuild if I touched assets / config / build settings?
- [ ] Verified the running app is the new binary, not cached?
- [ ] Updated this file if this was user-visible?

